The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR) in storage constrained databases, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed scheme also involves storage placement schemes, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the proposed scheme is inspired by the content placement scheme in coded caching, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.CC).
